The government of Ondo state has honoured an auto sports’ group ‘Work and Play’-the organisers of Ondo Autosport Rally- for their tourism drive and youth empowerment through their event. The award which was presented by the State’s Governor Honourable Lucky Orimisan Aiyedatiwa, on behalf of the governor, Arakunrin Rotimi Akeredolu during the closing races of the fifth Ondo Auto Rally in Akure at the weekend. While presenting the award to the President of the group, Adeoye Ojuoko, the deputy governor said: “The state is very pleased with what Adeoye and his Motorsports group is doing to the tourism space of the state.”   Ikoyi Club hails Leadway on tennis clinic     Golfers eagerly await DStv Premium Golf Day     Impressive Ofili named US Athlete of the Week   He said the State Governor directed that recognition award be given. “It is a show of endorsement and appreciation for the impact this event has had and the huge opportunities it brings with it every time in 7 is hosted,” he added. Ojuoko said that the award from the state will only spur him and his team to do more for the growth of the Autosport in the country: “I am indeed grateful for this honour and the level of support the government has extended to us and keep giving us. We will take this as a motivation to increase our footprint in the state.” Meanwhile, founder of Elizade group, Chief Michael Ade-Ojo said the youth in the state should leverage the opportunities presented by the event for economic empowerment including up skilling to be relevant in the Motoring industry.